author: IGN
description:
In today's Daily Fix:
The Walking Dead TV series had an impressive run with 11 seasons and more than 170 episodes. But even after that, plus six spin-off shows, executive producer Scott Gimple thinks there's still plenty of story to tell. Taking a cue from the France-set Daryl Dixon spin-off, the cast's core characters could find themselves all over the globe, with Gimple saying it could provide for 15 more years' worth of stories. In other news, Jar Jar Binks actor Ahmed Best is returning to the character in a one-shot comic. Star Wars: Jar Jar Binks will be co-written by Best, and will feature the character playing a pivotal role in the rebellion after Revenge of the Sith. And we’ve got a look at the thrills you can experience in The Isle of Berk at Universal Epic Universe.

Presented by Universal Orlando Resort and its new theme park, Universal Epic Universe.

#IGN
title: The Walking Dead Could Go On for Another 15 Years - IGN Daily Fix

description:
Don't miss the Official Trailer for The Family Plan 2, a family action comedy distributed by Apple TV starring Mark Wahlberg, Michelle Monaghan, Zoe Colletti, and more. Trouble in a European paradise awaits in The Family Plan 2, streaming exclusively on Apple TV on November 21.

Dan Morgan is many things: a devoted husband, a loving father, a celebrated car salesman. He’s also a former assassin. And when his past catches up to his present, he’s forced to take his unsuspecting family on a road trip unlike any other.

The Family Plan 2 stars Mark Wahlberg, Michelle Monaghan, Kit Harington, Zoe Colletti, Thomas Forbes-Johnson, Reda Elazouar, and more. The film is directed by Simon Cellan Jones and written by David Coggeshall. 

The Family Plan 2 streams exclusively on Apple TV on November 21.

author: IGN
description:
Don't miss the Official Trailer for Send Help, a darkly comedic psychological thriller distributed by 20th Century Studios starring Rachel McAdams, Dylan O'Brien, Edyll Ismail, and more. Two unlikely colleagues must set aside their grievances to survive a deserted yet sinister island in Send Help, in theaters on January 30, 2026.

Linda Liddle and Bradley Preston, two colleagues who find themselves stranded on a deserted island after they are the only survivors of a plane crash. On the island, they must overcome past grievances and work together to survive, but ultimately, it becomes an unsettling and darkly humorous battle of wills and wits to make it out alive. 

Send Help stars Rachel McAdams, Dylan O'Brien, Edyll Ismail, Dennis Haysbert, Xavier Samuel, Chris Pang, Thaneth Warakulnukroh, Emma Raimi, and more. The film is directed by Sam Raimi, alongside being executive produced by JJ Hook.

Send Help is in theaters on January 30, 2026.
title: Send Help - Official Trailer (2026) Rachel McAdams, Dylan O'Brien

author: IGN
description:
To the surprise of NO ONE, 2021's sneak-up horror hit The Black Phone got a sequel. Black Phone 2 finds the traumatized siblings, Finney and Gwen at a frost-bitten and remote campground when Ethan Hawke as the Grabber finds his way back to terrorizing the pair. Director Scott Derrickson and co-writer C. Robert Cargill are returning, as are Mason Thames and Madeleine McGraw as the two leads, but can that kind of continuity in the creative team keep Black Phone 2 from "horror sequel purgatory?" Or will it fall victim the curse of the cash-grabbing follow up in spite of a very Freddy Krueger like turn from the now paranormal Ethan Hawke villain?
 
Reviewer Matt Donato answers that question in his review out of Fantastic Fest, then sticks around for a chat after the review!

#IGN #Movies
title: Black Phone 2 Review

author: IGN
description:
DICE return with Battlefield 6, their latest entry in the long running Battlefield series. A return to the roots of the Bad Company meets Battlefield 4 is the aim, powered by Frostbite and a wide collection of collaboration studios. 

The technology footing was always strong, with destruction, large scale and multiplayer focus at its heart. We cover a range of PC hardware, high frame rates and even RTX Multi Frame Generation along with the good and bad within the engine and game in our IGN Battlefield 6 Performance review.

00:00 Introduction
00:43 Technical Engine focus and footing of the series
02:42 Menu options and options to play
03:23 Menu settings, scalability, PC configurations and optimal settings
07:07 High Refresh testing, input latency and MFG performance and visual comparison
11:02 High end RTX5080 Performance testing
11:47 Technical gremlins
13:40 Summary

#IGN #Battlefield6 #PerformanceReview
title: Battlefield 6 Performance Review

author: IGN
description:
Peacemaker Season 2 just ended its eight-episode run on HBO Max with a major turning point in the life of John Cena’s aspiring do-gooder Christopher Smith. Creator James Gunn teased that the finale would lay the groundwork for 2027’s Man of Tomorrow movie. And Gunn seems to have made good on that promise, with the finale strongly hinting at which character will serve as the common enemy uniting Nicholas Hoult’s Lex Luthor and David Corenswet’s Superman. So why are we so unhappy with the big reveal?

Let’s break down why Peacemaker Season 2’s finale doesn’t quite gel with the rest of the DCU. We’ll also explore the other big revelations in this episode, like the debut of Checkmate and the planet Salvation. Here’s everything you need to know about the ending of Peacemaker Season 2.
Peacemaker is created by James Gunn and stars John Cena, Danielle Brooks, Freddie Stroma, Jennifer Holland, Steve Agee, Frank Grillo, and Robert Patrick. The entire second season is now available to stream on
title: Peacemaker Season 2 Dropped a Major Man of Tomorrow Reveal, So Why Are We Disappointed?
